    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Iraq Crackup</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>David H Good letter criticizes Pres Bush's response to Congressional members opposed to troop buildup in Iraq</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Anti-Buildup Measure to Have Bipartisan Stamp'' (news article, Jan. 17):</p>
        <p>President Bush said, ''My only call to Congress is that if you've got a better way to succeed, step up and explain it.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Anti-Buildup Measure to Have Bipartisan Stamp'' (news article, Jan. 17):</p>
        <p>President Bush said, ''My only call to Congress is that if you've got a better way to succeed, step up and explain it.''</p>
        <p>This would seem to be somewhat analogous to Mr. Bush's telling people -- after he's totaled his car by crashing into a tree -- that they are not allowed to criticize his driving unless they first fix his car.</p>
        <p>David H. Good  New York, Jan. 17, 2007</p>
      </block>
